description: This file is a C header file defining the exported API functions for the Content Filtering HTTP Session Management Object. It includes function prototypes for creating, removing, enrolling, and initializing the object.

methods.name: CfHttpSmoComponentCreate
methods.description: Creates the Content Filtering HTTP Session Management Object component, accepting context and reserved handle arguments.

methods.name: CfHttpSmoCreate
methods.description: Creates an instance of the Content Filtering HTTP Session Management Object with specified contexts.

methods.name: CfHttpSmoRemove
methods.description: Removes the specified instance of the HTTP Session Management Object.

methods.name: CfHttpSmoEnrollObjects
methods.description: Enrolls necessary objects for the HTTP Session Management Object to function properly.

methods.name: CfHttpSmoInitialize
methods.description: Initializes the HTTP Session Management Object.
